FBIS4-34328 "drlat118_a_94019" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Bahrain Establishes Diplomatic Relations Bahrain Establishes Diplomatic Relations FL1806154894 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1000 GMT 18 Jun 94 FL1806154894 Havana Radio Progreso Network Spanish BFN [From the "First Thing" program] [Text] Cuba and Bahrain have signed a document establishing diplomatic relations at the ambassadorial level. The document also notes an interest in strengthening friendly and cooperative relations in different areas of interest. The document adds: This cooperation will be based on respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity, noninterference in the two countries' internal affairs, and the pledge to fulfill the UN goals and principles for consolidating international peace and security. The document was signed by Raul Barzaga, director of the Foreign Ministry's North Africa and Middle East Directorate, and (Raboul Rahman Salman Hadj), director of the Bahraini Foreign Ministry's international affairs.
